{"id":1736904,"retrievedAt":"2026-07-24T12:40:15.438Z","response":{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":null,"belongs_to_collection":null,"budget":0,"genres":[],"homepage":"","id":1736904,"imdb_id":null,"origin_country":["US"],"original_language":"en","original_title":"Ryan Aralyn","overview":"# English Translation  The story follows Ryan, who bears the responsibility of caring for his sick grandmother and his son Amir. Ryan works tirelessly to earn a living to support his family. His wife, Hanis, neglects her duties as a wife and constantly goes out at night to have fun. Aralyn was raised in a well-to-do family and plans to marry Zarul. Puan Nora is unhappy with Zarul's behavior and asks Aralyn to get to know his true character first. One day, Aralyn and Ryan collide in a road accident that causes Ryan to lose his son and Aralyn to become paralyzed. After the incident, Ryan's life continues to be tested when Hanis asks for a divorce and his grandmother passes away. Ryan is haunted by guilt towards Aralyn because the accident has left her paralyzed. Ryan goes to Kuala Lumpur to find Aralyn to apologize, but he is unable to face her as she is depressed about her inability to walk. Zarul cannot accept Aralyn's condition and decides to end their relationship.","popularity":0,"poster_path":"/29vaFAk3UaSXrNeRrHHpMPUVX19.jpg","production_companies":[{"id":140856,"logo_path":null,"name":"Qaisworks Production Sdn Bhd","origin_country":""}],"production_countries":[],"release_date":"2020-01-01","revenue":0,"runtime":0,"softcore":false,"spoken_languages":[],"status":"Released","tagline":"","title":"Ryan Aralyn","video":false,"vote_average":0,"vote_count":0,"alternative_titles":{"titles":[]},"credits":{"cast":[{"adult":false,"gender":2,"id":1279687,"known_for_department":"Acting","name":"Zul Ariffin","original_name":"Zul Ariffin","popularity":0.6211,"profile_path":"/wlMo5HslLGpZRqCBhYYIzmkKGit.jpg","cast_id":2,"character":"","credit_id":"6a62c7e85be1379b3075a5b6","order":0},{"adult":f